The paper discusses the detection of compromised accounts on social networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning and data analysis techniques to detect anomalies in user behavior suggests a focus on social network analysis (cs.SI) and data mining (cs.SD). The discussion of the impacts of compromised accounts on financial markets suggests a potential focus on cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the mention of detecting staged compromises for publicity reasons suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
